═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  admin_keys/ — Admin Console Keypair (Compile-Time)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  This directory holds the Ed25519 keypair for admin console
  authentication. BOTH keys are embedded into the unikernel
  binary at build time via include_str!() in src/admin/auth.rs.

  Files:
    admin_pub.pem    ← Ed25519 public key (verifies signatures)
    admin_priv.pem   ← Ed25519 private key (signs challenges)

  The private key is gitignored. Each deployment should have
  its own unique keypair.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  DEPLOYMENT WORKFLOW
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  1. Clone/download the project
  2. Run: ./scripts/gen-admin-keys.sh
     → Creates both keys in this directory
  3. Build: cargo build --target x86_64-unknown-hermit
     → Both keys are embedded in the binary
  4. Deploy the binary (QEMU, Digital Ocean, etc.)
  5. Open https://<appliance>/admin/ and click "Sign In"
     → No file picker. The browser auto-fetches the embedded
       private key and signs the challenge automatically.

  That's it. No hunting for key files.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  SECURITY MODEL
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Whoever builds the binary controls the keypair. The private
  key is baked into the appliance at build time and served to
  the admin console browser via HTTPS.

  The security boundary is network access to /admin/:
    - Only people who can reach the admin URL can authenticate
    - HTTPS protects the key in transit
    - Each deployment has a unique keypair

  For 1000 deployments, each operator:
    1. Downloads the project
    2. Drops their own keys into admin_keys/
    3. Builds → gets a unique binary with their own keys
    4. Deploys to their own server

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  GENERATING NEW KEYS
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Run the included script:

    ./scripts/gen-admin-keys.sh

  This generates both keys in this directory. After generating
  new keys, rebuild the binary to embed them.

